# Styling Conventions

## Tailwind Only

Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively — no CSS modules or inline `style` objects.

## Theme Colors

Colors are defined as CSS custom properties and consumed via `hsl(var(--token))`.
Never hardcode hex/rgb colors. Use semantic tokens:

`primary`, `secondary`, `destructive`, `muted`, `accent`, `checkin`,
`background`, `foreground`, `card`, `popover`, `border`, `ring`

```tsx
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground" />
<span className="text-destructive" />
```

## Dark Mode & Color Themes

- Dark mode uses the `class` strategy (`dark` class on `<html>`)
- Color themes are applied via `[data-theme="..."]` attribute on `<html>`

## Class Merging

Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge/conditionally apply classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
<div className={cn("rounded-lg p-4", isActive && "ring-2 ring-primary")} />
```

## Custom Utilities

- `.scrollbar-hidden` — hides scrollbar on overflow-scroll containers
- Use `cva` (class-variance-authority) for component variant styles (buttons, badges)

## Responsive

Mobile-first breakpoints. Use Tailwind `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` prefixes.
